).

DIFFERENTIAL DIAGNOSIS: The present species is placed in 

Pseudocrepidobothrium
Rego and Ivanov, 2001

(Proteocephalinae) because of the medullary position of the genital organs, the medullary and paramuscular position of vitellaria and the heart-shaped structure of suckers (
Freze, 1965
; 
Schmidt, 1986
; 
Rego and Ivanov, 2001
).
